1 the individual privacy interest clearly outweighs the merits of public disclosure.
2 (4) (A) The duration for which the executive exemption lasts is only as long as the protection
3 of the exempted information serves its underlying purpose.
4 (B) For exempted information that is not challenged in court or for which a court upholds the
5 executive exemption, then the exemption expires no later than the time at which the underlying issue is
6 resolved or after 60 days, whichever comes first.
7 (C) The executive exemption is waived at the time the information is voluntarily disclosed to a third
8 party to whom the executive exemption does not apply.
9 (5) For the purposes of this section, an individual privacy interest clearly outweighs the merits of
10 public disclosure as provided in 2-6-1002(1) only if the public information requested is confidential information
11 under the provisions of 2-6-1002(1)(a) through (1)(d) (1)(E).
