9 Section 3. Section 2-6-1009, MCA, is amended to read:
10 "2-6-1009. Written notice of denial -- failure to meet response deadline -- civil action -- costs to
11 prevailing party in certain actions to enforce constitutional or statutory rights. (1) A public agency that denies an
12 information request to release information or records shall provide a written explanation for the denial.
13 (2) If a person who makes an information request receives a denial from a public agency and
14 believes that the denial violates the provisions of this chapter, the person may file a complaint pursuant to the
15 Montana Rules of Civil Procedure in district court.
16 (3) If a person who makes an information request to an executive branch agency does not receive
17 a response from the agency as required in 2-6-1006(3), the person may file a complaint in district court.
